This will be the fourth challenge against the President who has been in power since 1986, the previous occasions being 2001, 2006 and 2016. Mr Kyagulanyi’s lawyers are racing against time because the law gives an aggrieved candidate a maximum of 15 days after the results have been released to file a petition.  National Unity Platform (NUP) party leader Robert Kyagulanyi, aka Bobi Wine, has notified the Supreme Court that he will file a petition on Monday challenging the re-election of President Yoweri Museveni.
This will be the fourth challenge against the President who has been in power since 1986, the previous occasions being 2001, 2006 and 2016. 



